Silene laciniata is a species of flowering plant in the family Caryophyllaceae. 
It is also known as the jagged-leaved or fringed campion. 
The plant typically grows to a height of 60 centimeters and features narrow, hairy, lance-shaped leaves. 
The flowers of this plant have five white petals, each deeply lobed giving the appearance of fringed edges. 
It blooms in late spring to early summer and can be found growing in rocky or gravelly soil, along trails, and near streams and rivers. 
The plant's roots have a taproot system that aids in its survival in dry conditions. 
Silene laciniata adds beauty to natural landscapes and can also be grown as an ornamental plant in gardens.
